Children of all ages will be thrilled to receive these delightful airplane toys!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Definitely worth the money
reviews.reviewText: This product is actually much better than I thought it was going to be after reading the comments. They are actually pretty thick and sturdy. Of course if you give it to a 3 yr old like I'm doing there is bound to be some broken propels. But let's be real I'm sure he could break them if they were made of metal. I love the bright colors and variety of plane styles. Definitely worth the money. They did leave out the O in police lol but who really care. Can't make everyone happy but I definitely am.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cheapy, But Fun
reviews.reviewText: My twin boys are obsessed with airplanes — I liked these because they include no sound/batteries/lights, yet they still are pull-back-and-release. My twins are three years old and are really rough on toys, so I knew that some of the plastic parts of these airplanes would inevitably break. For the price, I’d say this is a nice set of airplanes: just keep in mind they are a little cheapy and are bound to break with rougher play.
